  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Communications and Press</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Delivery of communications materials, outreach events, engagement with print and media activities on Irish Aid activities, and management of Irish Aid website and social media platforms</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Public Outreach activities will be targeted towards increasing awareness of Irish Aid&#x2019;s work among new audiences in Ireland, as well as increasing understanding of global development issues, and how Irish Aid&#x2019;s policies support and further the implementation of the Sustainable Development Goals. This will be achieved through: 1. Organisation of and participation in public events that attract a wide audience, including the 18-25 age group, increasing knowledge and understanding of Irish Aid and global development issues; 2. Strong Irish Aid presence on social media, including through the development and dissemination of video materials, interviews with volunteers and partners to demystify aspects of Irish Aid&#x2019;s work; 3. Engaging online presence through revamped Irish Aid website in responsive format optimised for mobile access, with stories and priorities clearly outlined supporting our policy documents; 4. Engagement with Irish and international media outlets on the work of Irish Aid and on global development themes.</narrative>
  </description>
